At least, 10 persons have reportedly died and 27 others seriously injured in a fetal road accident which occurred along Fika-Potiskum highway in Yobe State, Tuesday night. The accident happened when a pickup van conveying goods and passengers lost control and veered into a ditch along the highway. The victims mostly elderly and youths were all rescued and evacuated by the Marshals of the Federal Road Safety Commission (FRSC), Potiskum unit command, while the injured were all admitted and are now receiving treatment at the General hospital, Potiskum. According to the Driver of the vehicle who survived the accident, Malam Lawandi, the dead and the survivors were returning from Dogo Abare Market and were on their way to their hometown, Potiskum. “After overtaking a vehicle, my steering rod developed a problem and I lost control,” he recounted. Officials of Federal Road Safety had to struggle to pull the bodies out from the mangled vehicles. On learning about the incident, relatives of the victims who are mostly residents of Gadan Talakawa and Arara Biyu, Potiskum rushed to the spot. Meanwhile, Director Personnel Management, (DPM) Potiskum Local Government Area, Ibrahim Yayangida Abubakar, was in the hospital and assisted in paying for the prescribed drugs for the victims.